line_2: Our Heart-strings groan with deep Complaint,

line_1: And thrusting it beyond his Joint,
line_2: 'Tis done, He cry'd: I've gain'd my Point. —

line_1: The shapely limb and lubricated joint,
line_2: Within the small dimensions of a point,

line_1: To hear no motion made that's out of joint,
line_2: And when he spies his member, make his point.

line_1: Mangle each limb, and dislocate each joint;
line_2: Headlong they hurl him on some ice-rock's point,
